  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency support to mitigate the Impact of conflict on the lives and livelihoods of vulnerable communities in the Northern Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this $1.5 million FAO is to Mitigate the impact of conflict on the lives and livelihoods of vulnerable farming and pastoral communities in Northern Ethiopia. FAO and its partners will provide supplementary animal feed, deliver seeds of fast-growing improved fodder crops, and associated skills for households with access to irrigation facilities,  extension services, and tailored refresher training on good agronomic practices (GAP), post-harvest handling, fodder production, and value addition. Supplementary feed beneficiaries will also be trained on feed utilization, feed nutritional value, and benefits. FAO will also undertake rehabilitation of water harvesting facilities mainly ponds, provision of veterinary inputs and equipment, livestock treatment and vaccination services, and agricultural inputs for the upcoming irrigation and meher seasons. The project provides life-saving assistance to 552,212 people, including 164,803 women, 158,699 men, 146,491 girls, 140,387 boys, and 97,661 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
